  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9f\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bbf \u0b87\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8 - \u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b95\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No more token system at petrol stations - Kanchana Wijesekara",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Energy Kanchana Wijesekara has said that token system is not currently implemented at fuel filling stations by the Ministry of Energy.",
        "The token system was initially introduced to reduce the long queues seen on the 23rd and 24th of last month.",
        "\u201cThe token system was introduced to save the public from queuing and inform them to go to the filling station on July 11 or 15 when fuel is available. The system was launched only for those few days,\u201d .",
        "Minister Kanjana Wijesekhara said that currently the system of issuing tokens at fuel filling stations is being carried out without the intervention of the Ministry of Energy.",
        "Despite the minister's rejection of the continuation of the token system, many petrol stations have seen a significant influx of people waiting in line to get fuel."
      ],
